rom weak\ncoupling is actually ferromagnetism. We also discuss the effect of the edge\nfermions and show that they are unimportant in the asymptotic weak coupling\nlimit, but may give rise to, e.g., a charge-density-wave order at moderate\ncoupling strengths.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Jan 2014 21:02:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 28 Jan 2014 23:52:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-04-29"}
